description:
Labour Day is marked as a day where we celebrate the contributions of our workforce. For our workers who are performing essential services, there has not been a time in Singaporeâ€™s history that your contributions have been more vital to our survival.

Many people in our workforce will also face very difficult times ahead so we hope that this little show of support will give them a brighter horizon to look forward to.

We must bounce back stronger and do our best to leave no man behind.

We also want to say thank you to our migrant worker friends who have so often been overlooked in one way or another. It is and always will be a work in progress but we should never stop striving to do better by the ones who help build our homes. 

We hope you enjoy this video. It could not have been put together without the efforts of so many of you. Hopefully, this little labour of love will go the distance.

#homebutnotalonesg #stayhomeforsg #sgunited #wearemajulah

message: It was a typical bustling morning at Jurong West 505 Market but with a difference â€“a queue of calm, masked patrons patiently waiting to enter. Safe distancing seemed to have become instinctive. One by one, they underwent thermal screening and were offered hand sanitisers upon entering. Once inside, almost everyone kept their distance without further prompting, helped by reminders over the public announcement system. For the few who needed extra nudging, Enforcement Officers and SG Clean Ambassadors were there to ensure everyone keeps themselves and others safe. If you are planning to visit Jurong West 505 Market â€“ donâ€™t forget that entry is on alternate dates based on NRIC/FIN numbers. If your NRIC/FIN number ends with an odd last digit (1,3,5,7,9), you should visit on odd dates of the month while those with NRIC/FIN numbers ending with an even last digit (2,4,6,8,0) should visit on even dates. Remember to wear a mask before going out, make your grocery trips alone during non-peak hours, and continue to follow safe distancing measures. Let's do the right thing. The health of all depends on each one of us. #SGUnited #SGClean #StayHomeforSG

message: Labour Day is marked as a day where we celebrate the contributions of our workforce. For our workers who are performing essential services, there has not been a time in Singaporeâ€™s history that your contributions have been more vital to our survival. Many people in our workforce will also face very difficult times ahead so we hope that this little show of support will give them a brighter horizon to look forward to. We must bounce back stronger and do our best to leave no man behind. We also want to say thank you to our migrant worker friends who have so often been overlooked in one way or another. It is and always will be a work in progress but we should never stop striving to do better by the ones who help build our homes. We hope you enjoy this video. It could not have been put together without the efforts of so many of you. Hopefully, this little labour of love will go the distance. #homebutnotalonesg #stayhomeforsg #sgunited #wearemajulah Also if you enjoy this music, please look up the composer Jazz Chong. message: #YTPAlumniStayHomeShowcase 13 year old Chloe Chua is the darling of Singaporeâ€™s young classical music scene with many admiring followers. She was even slated to perform in a concert with the SSO this year, hopefully, we'll get to see her do just that after this is all over! Kudos to this winner of countless international competitions including the 2018 Yehudi Menuhin competition in Zurich. Besides playing the violin, Chloe also enjoys reading, swimming and skateboarding. "I have recently recorded from home, the Romance from Albumblatt, composed by Richard Wagner and arranged for the Violin and Piano by A. Wilhelm. I want to share this performance with everyone who is staying home during the Circuit Breaker period and I would also like to dedicate this performance especially to our medical frontline workers, who are fighting very hard daily to save peopleâ€™s lives and those who are suffering from Covid-19. I want to thank you for your dedication and selflessness. You have sacrificed your time, comfort and even put your own lives at risks for what you are doing. I hope that the Covid-19 can be contained very soon and life will be back to normal. Please stay safe and keep healthy. I hope my performance can bring joy and hope to everyone and YES! We can get through this tough time together!" - Chloe #StayHomeforSG #SGUnited

description:
Happy May Day to all!

This year, May Day takes on added significance with COVID-19. Workers, companies and unions are not only fighting the disease as one, but working together to ensure we keep Singapore running. Our tripartite spirit burns bright!
 
Exceptional times often inspire extraordinary actions. 

This May Day, I salute our frontline workers and migrant workers who have made many sacrifices and contributions to the country, as we fight COVID-19.
 
I also want to express my appreciation to all public officers, including from the Ministry of Communications and Information (MCI) family
â€“ our Cyber Security Agency of Singapore - CSA colleagues for keeping our networks secure; Singapore Post colleagues for keeping our essential postal services operating; librarians and volunteers from the National Library Board, Singapore for ensuring our patrons are digitally engaged even from their homes; and colleagues from Infocomm Media Development Authority - IMDA who are pressing on in our digital transformation efforts â€“ just to name a few. 

And to the many more who are working tirelessly for Singapore, thank you for keeping our country going as we put up our best fight against COVID-19. 

Happy May Day, everyone. Together, we can and will overcome!

You, me and we, playing our part in Total Defence.

Without you realising it, you may have already been doing so in your daily life.

Maybe itâ€™s Social Defence. You are part of a close-knit community of family, friends, neighbours and colleagues. You have strong bonds with people around you. You stay united as one people, and no attempts to sow discord and fear can divide you.  

Could it be Economic Defence? You not only contribute to the economy, but also actively keep your skills relevant and find better ways to perform your job. You commit to setting aside savings for a rainy day.

Civil Defence, perhaps? In an emergency, you may just be the first person to respond and help. You are prepared to take action, whether to save yourself, call for help or even save the people around you.

Or Military Defence? You are one of the million National Servicemen committed to the defence of our nation. Or you may be the parent, spouse, sibling or friend who has supported our National Servicemen in their duties. 

And then thereâ€™s Psychological Defence. You have the resilience to face challenges and overcome adversity. You are proud to call Singapore your home and you feel a need to speak up against negative comments about Singapore. You are ready to put your heart, mind and will to our defence! 

Yes, Singapore can be strong only if we all stand united and commit to play our part. 

We are Total Defence.

message: In support of the #MuseumFromHome movement, we are getting our staff to share their favourite artefact with you! â€œEvery time I enter the museum, Iâ€™ll usually make a quick stop at the gallery where Zubir Saidâ€™s baby grand piano is on display. The showcase is set up to look like Pak Zubirâ€™s home studio on Joo Chiat Road. As I picture him siting at the piano, Iâ€™m always struck by how this highly talented man, overcame so many odds in pursuit of his passion for music and the arts, yet he was so generous with his time and gifts, composing rousing songs to promote love and loyalty to Singapore, and still teaching music to children from his home. In these difficult times when so many things that we can usually take for granted are no longer easy to do or available to us, Iâ€™m reminded of how music can uplift the spirit, and at the end of a workday, I take joy in being with my family and singing songs from my childhood, including Pak Zubirâ€™s â€˜Semoga Bahagiaâ€™ to my baby.â€ #CultureCarriesOn #DoseOfCulture #MuseumsAndChill #MuseumFromHome #Enjoy_CityMuseums_From_Home #OurSGHeritage #GoDigital #SocialDistancing #StayHome #SGUnited #StayHomeforSG #MissOurMuseums

message: On this Labour Day, I would like to express my heartfelt thanks to our frontline workers who have been working tirelessly in the fight against COVID-19. In these difficult times, businesses and workers have been affected. To protect livelihoods, support businesses and help #Singaporeans, the Government has rolled out 3 budgets - the Unity, Resilience and Solidarity Budgets. We have also tapped on our national reserves, which our forefathers painstakingly built up, to overcome this crisis as a nation. Our aim is to bring down the number of community infections and progressively lift the "circuit breaker" measures so that our economy can gradually recover. As PM Lee Hsien Loong said in his May Day speech, some sectors can open up first and recover faster than others. As we press on with our fight against the virus, I urge everyone to do our part and support those who are working hard at the frontlines by continuing to #StayHomeforSG during the "circuit breaker" period. Together, we can defeat COVID-19. Wishing everyone a Happy and Healthy Labour Day! â€” Hong Tat [Photos taken before 21 March 2020]

message: "A lot of us are extremely privileged to have a roof over our heads, family around us, and food on the table, and I want to remind us How all this is possible. Our migrant worker brothers sacrifice family life to build our homes. Our government keeping us home, in order to flatten the curve, so that families stay virus free for each other, and the community. Our essential workers and businesses working harder than ever to make sure we have food and necessities to tide us through this crisis. Everyone has a part to play in breaking the coronavirus butterfly effect. These people have already done so much for us. All we need to do, is stay home. . I took this photo with my flag because even though not everybody living in Singapore is from Singapore, weâ€™re all in this together now, and we can use all the support we can get. So. I encourage you all to post a photo of our National Flag, and use the hashtags below, or hang out your flags, in support of our tiny Big Cityâ€™s valiant attempts to get through this uncertainty together. Majulah Singapura! . . . @wearemajulah #HomeButNotAloneSG #WeAreMajulah #StayHomeForSG #SGUnited" Thank you @caitofalltraits for sharing! We're enjoying seeing all the displays of your flags at home. Label: stayhomeforsg
message: Today is Labour Day. Let us spend a moment to think about those who are keeping Singapore going while many of us stay home. To all the people working on the frontline, and those performing essential services across Singapore, we are deeply appreciative of your sacrifices and hard work in safeguarding our country. I also want to thank our Enforcement Officers and Ambassadors from almost 50 agencies who are walking the ground every day to ensure safe distancing in public spaces. Including Labour Day today! Let us make their collective contributions worthwhile. During this circuit breaker period, we can make a positive difference every day through our daily choices. Like staying at home, and putting on a mask when we need to go out for essentials, and going out alone where possible. Let us keep up the good fight so we can stop COVID-19 and emerge stronger together. Stay home, stay safe. Happy Labour Day! #StayHomeForSG #SGTogether #SGUnited #COVID19

description:
Dear Residents,

The outbreak of COVID-19 has changed our way of life. As we do our part by staying home, let us take this opportunity to cheer each other on in Changi Simei.

We invite you to send us photos of you at home with a few words of encouragement for fellow residents. We will compile the photos into a Facebook album and let fellow residents know that we are behind each other in these challenging times. 

Email photos to: photo@changisimei.sg
Closing date: 3 May 2020

I look forward to receiving your photos.  

Let us stand as One Changi Simei. 
Together we can overcome this outbreak as One Singapore.

#sgunited #onechangisimei #stayhomesg
